equilibrium.documentation: Description of a 2D, axi-symmetric, tokamak equilibrium; result of an equilibrium code.

equilibrium.code.documentation: Generic decription of the code-specific parameters for the code that has produced this IDS

equilibrium.code.output_flag.documentation: Output flag : 0 means the run is successful, other values mean some difficulty has been encountered, the exact meaning is then code specific. Negative values mean the result shall not be used.

equilibrium.code.parameters.documentation: List of the code specific parameters in XML format

equilibrium.ids_properties.documentation: Interface Data Structure properties. This element identifies the node above as an IDS

equilibrium.ids_properties.comment.documentation: Any comment describing the content of this IDS

equilibrium.ids_properties.creation_date.documentation: Date at which this data has been produced

equilibrium.ids_properties.homogeneous_t.documentation: 1 if the time of this IDS is homogeneous. In this case, the time values for this IDS are stored in ../time just below the root of this IDS. Otherwise, the time values are stored in the various time fields at lower levels in the tree.

equilibrium.ids_properties.provider.documentation: Name of the person in charge of producing this data

equilibrium.ids_properties.source.documentation: Source of the data (any comment describing the origin of the data : code, path to diagnostic signals, processing method, ...)
